{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Merge G3+G4 into one container call per bin (2N -> N)\n\n## Why\nG3 (child-coverage) and G4 (child-consistency) share the identical (parent, child, roster) context and are\ndisjoint audits the container prompt already describes together. Evaluating both in one call halves container\ncalls (2N -> N).\n\n## What\n- Evaluate G3 AND G4 in ONE call per (child/bin): present both rubrics over the shared context (`passes.py` +\n  `plan_review_container.md`). Keep per-criterion attribution in the output (findings tagged G3 vs G4).\n- Gate behind an OFFLINE EVAL confirming combined-call findings match separate-call findings within tolerance\n  (two rubrics in one turn must not dilute either).\n\n## Scope\n- In: the merged G3+G4 container call + attribution + the offline eval.\n- Out: parallelization (S3, dependency); bin-packing (S5).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] G3 and G4 are evaluated in one call per bin; findings are correctly attributed to G3 vs G4.\n- [ ] An offline eval shows no accuracy regression vs separate G3/G4 calls (within tolerance).\n- [ ] Container call count halves (2N -> N) for an epic; `make lint` + tests pass.\n\n## Remediation (opus review — MAJOR 5/7, BLOCKER 3)\n- Attribution flips from code-assigned (`passes.py:276` hardcodes `[cid]`) to model-self-reported. VALIDATE the\n  returned `criteria` against {G3,G4} and DROP out-of-set tags (mirror passes.py:222-224); preserve the\n  `_container_child` provenance (passes.py:288).\n- Update the sizing.py container-cost projection from `2N` to `N` calls (it currently hardcodes 2*children).\n- Fidelity gate = the S6 semantic eval harness (DEPENDS ON S6), not a vague \"offline eval\".\n- [ ] Merged-call findings with `criteria` not in {G3,G4} are dropped (not mis-tagged); `_container_child` preserved.\n- [ ] sizing.py container-cost projection reflects N calls (post-merge); shedding stays calibrated.\n- [ ] The S6 fidelity harness shows merged-call findings within tolerance of separate G3/G4 calls.\n\n## CI/eval posture (S6)\n- The S6 semantic fidelity eval is a HUMAN-REVIEWED development gate run before merge (live, opt-in), NOT a required/blocking CI check (non-deterministic). The offline eval-spec discipline check still runs on every PR.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782562205786976001,"uuid":"023eaafe-e34a-4dcb-82b5-bdd07c2cda1a"}